<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Embassy of Nepal in Brazil</title>

<style>
body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #f4f4f4;
}

/* HEADER */
header {
  background: #b22222;
  color: white;
  padding: 15px;
  text-align: center;
}

header img {
  width: 60px;
  vertical-align: middle;
}

header h1 {
  display: inline;
  margin-left: 10px;
}

/* NAV */
nav {
  background: #003893;
  padding: 10px;
  text-align: center;
}

nav a {
  color: white;
  margin: 0 15px;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-weight: bold;
}

/* HERO */
.hero {
  background: url('https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/12/Mount_Everest_as_seen_from_Drukair2_PLW_edit.jpg') center/cover;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 80px 20px;
}

/* CONTAINER */
.container {
  padding: 30px;
}

/* CARDS */
.card {
  background: white;
  padding: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  border-left: 6px solid #b22222;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}

/* GRID */
.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  gap: 20px;
}

/* IMAGE CARD */
.img-card img {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 8px;
}

/* BUTTON */
.btn {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 10px 15px;
  background: #003893;
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
}

/* FOOTER */
footer {
  background: #111;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 15px;
}
</style>

</head>

<body>

<header>
  <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9b/Flag_of_Nepal.svg">
  <h1>Embassy of Nepal in Brazil</h1>
  <p>Official Diplomatic Mission</p>
</header>

<nav>
  <a href="#home">Home</a>
  <a href="#services">Services</a>
  <a href="#mission">Mission</a>
  <a href="#news">News</a>
  <a href="#gallery">Gallery</a>
  <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
</nav>

<section class="hero">
  <h2>Strengthening Nepal–Brazil Relations</h2>
  <p>Consular Services • Cultural Exchange • Diplomacy</p>
</section>

<div class="container">

  <div class="card" id="home">
    <h2>Welcome</h2>
    <p>The Embassy of Nepal in Brazil promotes diplomatic relations, provides consular services, and supports citizens and visitors.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" id="services">
    <h2>Consular Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Visa Application</li>
      <li>Passport Services</li>
      <li>Document Authentication</li>
    </ul>
    <a class="btn" href="#contact">Start Application</a>
  </div>

  <div class="card" id="mission">
    <h2>Diplomatic Mission</h2>
    <p>The Embassy works to strengthen political, economic, and cultural relations between Nepal and Brazil, fostering cooperation and mutual understanding.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" id="news">
    <h2>Latest News</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Embassy Event</h3>
        <p>Recent cultural event promoting Nepalese heritage in Brazil.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Diplomatic Meeting</h3>
        <p>Meeting between Nepalese and Brazilian officials.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Public Notice</h3>
        <p>New updates on consular services and visa policies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" id="gallery">
    <h2>Gallery</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="img-card">
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/12/Mount_Everest_as_seen_from_Drukair2_PLW_edit.jpg">
      </div>
      <div class="img-card">
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/56/Kathmandu_Durbar_Square.jpg">
      </div>
      <div class="img-card">
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Lumbini_Birthplace_of_Buddha.jpg">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" id="contact">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p><strong>Ambassador:</strong> Nirmal Raj Kafle</p>
    <p>Email: info@nepalembassy.gov.np</p>
    <p>Location: Brasília, Brazil</p>
  </div>

</div>

<footer>
  <p>© 2026 Embassy of Nepal in Brazil</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
